{"id": "EUVD-2025-205113", "enisaUuid": "a529993e-e273-3a84-9c35-4f00cacf7a3a", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nio_uring: fix memory leak when removing provided buffers\n\nWhen removing provided buffers, io_buffer structs are not being disposed\nof, leading to a memory leak. They can't be freed individually, because\nthey are allocated in page-sized groups. They need to be added to some\nfree list instead, such as io_buffers_cache. All callers already hold\nthe lock protecting it, apart from when destroying buffers, so had to\nextend the lock there.", "datePublished": "2025-12-24T12:30:28", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-24T12:30:29", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-54041", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ac48787f58d1068f4e06d627c1135784d64b4c72", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b4a72c0589fdea6259720375426179888969d6a2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c117c15927772d1624c29c092b6bd3f47c7faa48"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-54041", "GHSA-g296-6qj4-g8f8"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "156ab682-8725-3ed9-a9a0-0613096bf3fd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "cc3cec8367cba76a8ae4c271eba8450f3efc1ba3 <b4a72c0589fdea6259720375426179888969d6a2"}, {"id": "3aa46113-0ba9-3e24-983f-58b2a446d563", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "5e915890-7014-3c2c-bf7d-eabea9506ae2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.24"}, {"id": "62d7abc3-1127-3d55-a041-1086ede7460f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.3"}, {"id": "dccff113-2422-33e4-a249-a2625492f7a7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.18"}, {"id": "e860d30b-5b4f-3ea7-bdc5-c28e99db93cd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2.11"}, {"id": "f9677f01-e114-375b-859f-4604507d0b7d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "cc3cec8367cba76a8ae4c271eba8450f3efc1ba3 <c117c15927772